<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980611.0001 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hke061082 - Thai Board of Investment Unveils New Promotion Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Under the new strategy, more activities will enjoy the
privilege of BOI promotion, which designed to boost Thai exports.
</P>
<P>
In a separate BOI press release, the board announced that
logistics activities, cultivation utilizing hydroponics, which
aims to encourage exports of Thai vegetables, and rebuilding of
automotive parts and engines for exports will be eligible for BOI
promotion.
</P>
<P>
The BOI is also considering to add agriculture and
agro-industry activities into the list of eligible activities for
BOI promotion.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, measures are taken by the BOI to address the soaring
unemployment.
</P>
<P>
Projects, which export no less than 80 percent of total sale
and increase employment by at least 500 employees or 50 percent
from the prior level, could enjoy income tax waiver from 3 to 5
years.
</P>
<P>
To encourage foreign companies to play a greater role in the
export of Thai goods, the alien business law will be revised or a
decree be issued, allowing foreign companies to engage in
businesses that promote Thai exports, the BOI said in the press
release.
</P>
<P>
The BOI is also intended to create an environment to revive
the real estate sector by enabling foreign companies to purchase a
specified number of existing buildings within a given time frame.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
