<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Apartment Fire Kills 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A midnight fire in a shabby apartment
house killed eight people including two women in the eastern
German city of Bochum, with only five residents surviving the
flames Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Three of the dead were found to be tenants, while the
identities of other bodies remained unclear. Tramps often slept in
the three-storied building in a working-class quarter of the city,
it was reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the firefighters, They found the stairwell in
flames and the egress blocked for residents when arriving there.
</P>
<P>
They also assumed that the people were asleep and had little
chance to escape when the fire broke out.
</P>
<P>
All five survivers were taken to hospital for smoke inhalation
treatment, with none of them in critical condition. Four of the
people were evacuated by firefighters and one jumped to safety
from a first-floor window, suffering only minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the midnight fire was still under investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
