<HEADLINE> Ties With China Important for S. African Economy: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- South African-Chinese
relations were important for South African trade and exports as
China's trade with South Africa were growing quickly, Trade and
Industry Minister Alec Erwin said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
China could soon rise from its current position as South
Africa's sixth largest trading partner to its fifth or fourth
largest partner, Erwin said in parliament.
</P>
<P>
China was currently ranked 30th largest trading nations in the
world, and it had the potential to enter the ranks of the top 25
soon, Erwin said.
</P>
<P>
Establishing diplomatic relations with China in January this
year had been an important political milestone, and it would also
bring in significant trade and investment benefits, he said.
</P>
<P>
Trade with China, including Hong Kong, totaled 8 billion Rand
(1.6 billion U.S. Dollars) in 1996, and China was the
11th-largest source of foreign investment in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Erwin said negotiations on a trade agreement with China were
underway, following his recent visit to China.
</P>
<P>
A technical team would return to China in the near future to
conclude the agreement and related matters, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
