<HEADLINE> Indian PM Appeals For Contribution For Relief Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee appealed Wednesday to Indians and those of Indian
origin living abroad to make generous contributions for relief
work in the cyclone-hit areas of the west coast.
</P>
<P>
According to an official press release issued Wednesday
evening, Vajpayee said that the severe cyclonic storm which hit
the coastal states of Gujarat, Maharashtra and Rajasthan caused
large-scale destruction of life and property.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports said that at least 283 people were killed and
more than 500 others injured and more than 15,000 people were
rendered homeless in the storm which run at the speed of 70 to 150
kilometers per hour from 10:30 a.m. Tuesday till Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Prime Minister directed the authorities to provide
all help and assistance to the marooned.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Indian Air Force (IAF) said here that IAF
helicopters and transport aircraft have been pressed into service
for aerial survey and relief operations in the affected areas.
</P>
