<HEADLINE> OAU to Set 10% Budget for African Economic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUADADOUGOU, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) Wednesday decided to set aside 10 percent of its
regular budget to finance the activities of the African Economic
Community (AEC).
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the OAU General Secretariat will also
prepare a detailed budget and submit it for consideration by the
policy organs of the OAU which have the responsibility for
approving the budget.
</P>
<P>
According to a decision adopted at the second ordinary session
of the 34th assembly of heads of state and government and made
public Wednesday, the OAU general secretariat should also
streamline the activities of the AEC as a way of achieving
efficiency in resource utilization.
</P>
<P>
A plan will also be worked out to ensure the complete freedom
of movement of persons throughout the community and officials of
the AEC and Regional Economic Communities (RECS) and holders of
the official travel documents of these institutions should be
exempt from visa requirements during travels within member
states, the decision says.
</P>
<P>
Member states should ensure the effective implementation of
the programs of the RECS as a way of facilitating the attainment
of the objectives of the AEC.
</P>
<P>
Regarding industrial policies and strategies, all member
states and RECS are called upon to ensure the harmonization of
their industrial development plans with the Alliance for Africa's
Industrialization (AAI).
</P>
<P>
Member states are also requested to create or strengthen
consultative mechanisms between the government and the private
sector with a view to formulating industrial development policies
and strategies in line with the objectives of their economic and
social development plans as well as programs for regional and
sub-regional economic integration and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Public sector should also be restructured to enable it to
improve its performance, modernize its management and stimulate
competitiveness in order to be in position to assist the private
sector in its industrialization endeavor.
</P>
<P>
Feasibility study will be conducted for the establishment of
the African Energy Commission for working out energy policies and
strategies.
</P>
<P>
The proposal for an OAU/EU summit in the year 2000 was
accepted, and the offer by the government of Egypt to host it was
welcomed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
