the maritime transit enterprise to facilitate the transportation
of goods from Djibouti port into the hinterland, Genna said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has become a landlocked country since the
independence of Eritrea in 1993. It uses both Assab port of
Eritrea and Djibouti port as its outlets for export produce.
</P>
<P>
However, the present border conflict between Ethiopia and
Eritrea has made the Assab port unavailable for Ethiopia's
export.
</P>
<P>
Genna expressed his conviction that Ethiopia would overcome
the problem that arose from the border crisis. 
