<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Inflation up in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's year-on-year inflation is
now creeping towards the 30 percent level, after pegging at 29.3
percent for May, the highest since April 1993.
</P>
<P>
This was 2.9 percentage points up from April level of 26.4 percent
according to the Central Statistical Office's latest review on price
trend released here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Inflation had been on the high side since the beginning of the
year with the first quarter of this year having averaged over 25
percent.
</P>
<P>
There has been an upsurge in the consumer prices for all item
categories except for drinks and tobacco, according to the
statistical office.
</P>
<P>
Increases in the consumer price indexes for clothing and footwear,
food and furniture contributed more to the hike in inflation in May.
</P>
</TEXT>
