<HEADLINE> Half Retrenched Workers Re-employed in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Over half of the 45,303
workers retrenched in Malaysia since the beginning of the regional
financial crisis in July 1997 till May 1998 have found employment,
according to the latest issue of an official labor market report
made available Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 23,373 workers or 51 percent of the workers
retrenched during the period have been re-employed, according to
the report compiled by the Human Resources Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the report said a total of 67,492 vacancies were
registered at the Manpower Department and labor offices nationwide
during the period.
</P>
<P>
It said that during the first six months of this year, 33,510
workers were retrenched with locals making up 89 percent and
foreign workers 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
The report said the retrenchment exercise involved 1,754
employers and many of them were in Peninsular Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the majority of the workers retrenched
during the period under review came from the manufacturing sector
which accounted for 51.1 percent of the total retrenched. 
</P>
</TEXT>
