<HEADLINE> Famine, Cholera Kill Many in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Reports from different regions
of Somalia indicate that famine and cholera are serious, killing
a lot of Somalis in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
According to the Rahanwein Resistance Army (RRA) humanitarian
secretary, more than 50,000 people in 11 villages surrounding the
twon of Baidoa are now being stricken by famine and severe
diarrhoea.
</P>
<P>
RRA humanitarian secretary, Sheikh Qasim Ibrahum Nur, said the
worst affected areas are the villages of Seydhelow and Bulo
Barakow, about 40 Km South of Baidoa, where dozens of people have
fallen for the diarrhoea with no one to treat them.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Qasim also said that three people died for famine at
Hobashile village near Baidoa town two days ago.
</P>
<P>
In Middle Shabelle region controlled by Somali Factional
leader Ali Mahdi Mohamed, more than 90 people died of cholera
in the past four weeks.
</P>
<P>
According to the regional governor, Nur Mohamed Shirbow, 73
people have died in the district of Warsheikh, 100 km Northeast
of Mogadishu alone, while 10 more have died in Adaleh district
and two in Run Nirgod town, all in Middle shabelle region.
</P>
<P>
Shirbow also spoke about serious food shortage in the region
following the floods, rats and locusts that attacked mainly the
rain-fed farms in the region.
</P>
<P>
He appealed the international comunity to come out for
helping the helpless Somalis in Middle Shabelle region at this
crucial moment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
