<HEADLINE> 100 Puzzles Listed By Chinese Scientists (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The following are the major
scientific puzzles which will challenge the 21st century,
according to Chinese scientists:
</P>
<P>
1. The Exploration of Substance Structure.
</P>
<P>
2. Difficulties in Harmonizing Relativity with Quantum Theory
</P>
<P>
3. Detection of Gravity Waves
</P>
<P>
4. The "Crisis" of Proton Spin and Experimental Detection
</P>
<P>
5. The Central Puzzle in Mechanics-Turbulence
</P>
<P>
6. The Quantum Size Effect and Superconductivity
</P>
<P>
7. Electrical Hyper-Conductivity at High Temperatures
</P>
<P>
8. Failure of Solids
</P>
<P>
9. Formation of the Cosmos and the Origin of Galaxies
</P>
<P>
10. The Solar Neutrino Mystery
</P>
<P>
11. Energy Source and Evolution of Nucleus-Active Galaxies
</P>
<P>
12. Formation of Interstellar Clouds and Stars
</P>
<P>
13. The Puzzle of the Universe Constant
</P>
<P>
14. Origin of Solar Activities
</P>
<P>
15. Magnetron Debate
</P>
<P>
16. Identification of Black Holes
