<HEADLINE> Fighting Breaks out in Ethio-Eritrean Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian government
spokesperson announced that a new attack of fighting broke out
early Thursday morning between the Ethiopian and Eritrean troops at
the eastern border with Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson said that the new attack on the area south of
Assab port was launched by the Eritrean forces. However, she did
not give any details of the new fighting.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson also said the fighting on the Badme-Shiraro
front, the main centers in the disputed 400 square km triangle of
land along their common border, has continued since Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The three day fighting since Tuesday was joined by only ground
forces of both sides, she said, adding that so far there was not
air raid in the fighting.
</P>
<P>
Since ground fighting resumed Tuesday, the Ethiopian and
Eritrean forces have fought on Badme-Shiraro front and eastern
border front (south of Assab). 
</P>
</TEXT>
