<HEADLINE> Macao Office of Preparatory Committee Secretariat Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Preparatory Committee of the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SARPC) inaugurated its Macao
secretariat office Thursday to canvas opinions from all quarters
of Macao.
</P>
<P>
The main task of the Macao office is to provide help to SARPC
members, to serve as a liaison and reception office. It also
handles letters and visits from local residents, said Chen Ziying,
secretary-general of the SARPC, who unveiled the name plaque of
the office here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Established last May in Beijing, the SARPC is responsible for a
series of issues for the founding of the Macao Special
Administrative Region. They include the formation of the first
Macao SAR government, the first legislature and the judiciary
bodies of the SAR.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that to accomplish these tasks, it is necessary to
listen to opinions and suggestions from Macao residents.
</P>
<P>
"The setting up of the Macao secretariat office will help (the
SARPC) listen to the opinions and proposals of Macao residents so
that decisions made by the SARPC will be in better keeping with
the actual situation in Macao, and better represent the wills of
Macao residents," he said. 
</P>
