<HEADLINE> Astrophysical Center Established in Beijing University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- An astrophysical center was set up
here today by the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) and Beijing
University, the most prestigious university in China.
</P>
<P>
The CAS-Peking (Beijing) University Joint Beijing Astrophysical
Center (CAS-PKU BAC) was launched by the Beijing Observatory under
the CAS and the university's Astrophysics Department.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen Jiansheng, director of the center and an
academician with the CAS, scientists at home and abroad can apply
for conducting their own research projects at the center. In
addition to astrophysical studies of its own, the center will also
be used to train postgraduates. 
</P>
