<HEADLINE> Asia's First Visa Cash Hybrid Card Launched in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of East Asia Limited,
The University of Hong Kong and Visa International launched
Thursday the HKU Smart Card -- the first Visa Cash hybrid card
available in the Asia Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The HKU Smart Card contains a contact chip, contactless chip
and magnetic stripe. This allows a single card to perform a
comprehensive range of financial functions, including stored value
and debit payments, ATM cash withdrawals and bank account
management.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the card performs an access control function. With
each card featuring the cardholder's photograph, faculty name and
staff or student number, it can also be used for identification on
campus.
</P>
<P>
"By integrating financial applications and other nonpayment
functions onto one card, we are offering the HKU Smart Card
holders convenience, security and global utility, and reaffirming
Visa's mission to offer the latest chip card technology," said
Dennis M. Goggin, president of Visa International (Asia Pacific),
at the card unveiling ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Starting Thursday, over 20,000 HKU staff and students will be
able to use the HKU Smart Card to access services and provide
identification on campus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
