<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets JCP Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a standing committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), today extended congratulations on
the normalization of the relations between CPC and the Japanese
Communist Party (JCP).
</P>
<P>
Hu met here this afternoon with a JCP delegation headed by
Nishiguchi Hikaru, member of the Secretariat and head of the
International Department of the JCP Central Committee, who held
talks with CPC officials on the issue of normalizing bilateral
ties in Beijing from June 8 to 10.
</P>
<P>
Hu voiced the hope that both CPC and JCP would foster a new
type of party-to-party relationship of cooperation in the spirit
of ending the past and ushering in the future and on the basis of
the principles of party-to-party relations confirmed by both
sides.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the two parties would
contribute to the promotion of long-term, stable and sound growth
of good-neighborly and friendly ties between China and Japan and
to the peace and stability in Asia and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Hikaru said Japan and China are friendly neighbors and JCP and
CPC had once enjoyed traditional friendship. JCP is ready to make
unremitting efforts for growth of the friendly and cooperative
relations between the two parties and two peoples, he told Hu.
</P>
<P>
Hikaru said that Fuwa Tetsuzo, head of the Presidium of the JCP
Central Committee, is looking forward to visiting China, and Hu
extended welcome to this.  
</P>
