<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Global Chinese Conference on
Computer in Education opened in the Chinese University of Hong
Kong here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference drew specialists and scholars from
China's mainland, Hong Kong, Taiwan and the United States,
Australia and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 articles on the theory and methods on computer
application in education will be presented at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Following the inaugural conference in May last year in
Guangzhou, this year's conference will provide a platform for
Chinese scholars and experts around the world who are involved in
educational sciences, computing sciences and other
computer-related areas to exchange their ideas and share their
experiences in computer and information technology.
</P>
<P>
Participants were specially interested in the situation in the
Hong Kong Special Administration Region (SAR). The SAR government
has planned a considerable amount of fresh investment in promoting
information science and technology education in primary and
secondary schools. 
