<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Thursday in thin trading on
selling pressure.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index eased 6.86
points to 483.00, the all-share Emas Index slipped 1.92 points to
124.35, the Industrial Index dipped 10.43 points to 961.97 and the
Second Board Index shed 0.93 points to 106.64.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 410 to 130, while 183 counters were
unchanged and 197 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover rose to 129.984 million shares valued at
296.947 million ringgit (75.214 million U.S. dollars) from 111.403
million shares worth 281.603 million ringgit (71.32 million
dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the main board rose to 122.449 million shares worth
286.603 million ringgit (72.594 million dollars) from Wednesday's
104.198 million shares valued at 271.586 million ringgit (68.79
million dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the second board, turnover increased to 7.535 million shares
valued at 10.344 million ringgit (2.62 million dollars) from 7.205
million shares worth 10.018 million ringgit (2.537 million
dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals stood at 8.508 million shares worth 20.426
million ringgit (5.173 million dollars) from 10.747 million shares
valued at 27.738 million ringgit (7.025 million dollars)
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 4.344
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
5.405 million shares, construction 9.231 million shares,
trading/services 51.059 million shares, infrastructure 1.741
million shares, finance 22.219 million shares, hotels 365,000
shares, properties 11.875 million shares, plantation 5.069 million
shares, mining 263,000 shares, trusts 111,000 shares, closed/fund
31,000 shares and loans 10.734 million shares. 
