<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Military Officer Meets U.S. Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of
General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, met with
James Schear, U.S. deputy assistant secretary of defense, and his
party here today.
</P>
<P>
Schear was here for a seminar on humanitarian assistance and
disaster relief between the two armed forces, which was held
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Xiong said that military relations are an important part of the
Sino-U.S. relationship, and that relations between the two armed
forces will develop further thanks to the growth of the bilateral
relationship.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two militaries have been actively implementing
an agreement reached by heads of state of the two countries since
President Jiang Zemin's successful visit to the United States last
October.
</P>
<P>
He added that relations between the two armed forces have
entered a new phase of development. He said that defense ministers
of the two countries will hold their first annual meeting in
Beijing next month.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the two sides inform each other of their
respective activities in humanitarian assistance and disaster
relief and share experience in this area not only demonstrates an
important action in implementing agreement reached by heads of the
two countries, but signals a major step toward advancing
military-to-military relations and enhancing mutual trust and
exchanges, Xiong said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
