<HEADLINE> Share Prices Gain on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices recovered Thursday
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index (STII) gained 19.02 points to close at 1,086.83 points
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the trading session, share prices finished higher
than Wednesday when STII plunged to a nine-year low.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume increased to 127.26 million units, valued
at 243.69 million Singapore dollars (140.86 million U.S. dollars).
There were 106 rises against 173 falls while 311 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Easyknit remained the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 9.60 million units. It was followed by
Magnum which had 8.51 million shares traded. SingTel remained the
third to have 6.68 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH topped the gainers list of the day as it rose by 1.10
Singapore dollars to finish at 12.60 Singapore dollars. SIA F
increased by 35 cents to end at 8.60 Singapore dollars. DBS F was
up by 25 cents to close at 9.65 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.00 Singapore dollar to end at 26.90 Singapore
dollars. Asean lost 80 cents and closed at 5.70 U.S. dollars.
CenProp was next which fell by 40 cents to finish at 9.70
Singapore dollars. 
</P>
