<HEADLINE> 38 Injured by Train Crash in Southwestern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-eight people were injuried,
some seriously, as one train rammed into another in Kochi
Prefecture, southwestern Japan, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
One of two one-car, diesel-powered trains involved in the
accident around 9:40 a.m. local time, was stalled on the
single-track Tosa Kuroshio line due to a fuel leak.
</P>
<P>
About 40 passengers and a driver were on the train stuck in the
mountain area of the prefecture, said a Kyodo News report.
</P>
<P>
The other train, with four repair workers and one driver
aboard, was initially sent to rescue the stalled one. 
</P>
