<HEADLINE> Share Prices Gain on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices recovered Thursday
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index (STII) gained 19.02 points to close at 1,086.83.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the trading session, share prices finished higher
than Wednesday when STII plunged to a nine-year low.
</P>
<P>
Share prices rebounded from morning losses to end higher after
a week of selling as concerns mounted over Asia's deepening
economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
However, dealers said they feared gains might not be sustained
given nagging concerns that a weak Japanese yen would undermine
China's competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
