<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Chamber Orchestra to Perform in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- World renowned conductor cum
piano soloist Philippe Entremont will lead the Israel Chamber
Orchestra to perform an all Beethoven program in Hong Kong on June
21, the Provisional Urban Council of Hong Kong announced here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Philippe Entremont, an artist of remarkable technique and
distinctive style both at the piano keyboard and on the podium,
started his professional debut in 1953 in Barcelona, Spain, when
he was 16.
</P>
<P>
He became the first laureate and Grand Prix winner of the
Marguerite Long-Jacques Thibaud Competition in 1956. He has
conducted world famous orchestras such as the Royal Philharmonic,
National Orchestra of France, Vienna Symphony Orchestra and many
others.
</P>
<P>
The Israel Chamber Orchestra, founded in 1965 and known as
Israel Chamber Ensemble, consists of 40 musicians. Its repertoire
ranges from early baroque to contemporary music. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
