<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabian Coach Afraid of Nobody </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia will take on Denmark in a
Group C match at Lens on Friday and their coach said he was not afraid
of any particular opponents.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Alberto Parreira, who led Brazil to take their fourth World
Cup trophy four years ago in the United States, said after a
training session:"I'm ont afraid of any particular opponents. All
four teams, whether strong or less so, have a chance. Obviously,
France will be favorites playing at home with the public behind
them. That will be our most difficult match, but it's the same for
the other teams."
</P>
<P>
"The preparation is over, we're ready. And when I say we're
ready, I mean that we have no injuries, no particular problems,
we're OK." Parreira said.
</P>
<P>
"Our first match is so important and in fact this encounter with
Denmark is our final in a way. A good result would give us
confidence for the remainder of the competition and possibly aim for
first place in the group." said Perreira.
</P>
<P>
The group also includes South Africa who will play hosts France
at Marseille on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
