<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Estrada on Philippine-China Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President-elect Joseph
Estrada said here Thursday that the friendly relations between his
country and China will develop further after he takes office later
this month.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Xie Fei, vice chairman of the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress of China, Estrada said that the
relations between the Philippines and China have been developing
steadily since the two nations established diplomatic relations in
1975.
</P>
<P>
Estrada, who was elected in the May 11 presidential elections,
expressed his wish that he could pay a visit to China as soon as
possible after he takes office on June 30.
</P>
<P>
China's economy has been developing very fast in recent years
and its achievements in the agricultural sector are particularly
remarkable, he said, adding that the Philippines and China could
learn from each other and cooperate closely in this sector.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei said that China attaches great importance to the
development of its relations with the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Xie said that he believes the bilateral ties will become
stronger during Estrada's six-year term as president.
</P>
<P>
Xie arrived here Wednesday to attend the centennial
independence celebrations in the Philippines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
