<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Youngest Player at France'98 not Overawed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Samuel Eto'o of Cameroon is the
youngest player at France'98 World Cup finals. Yet the 17-year-old
player said he was not a bit overawed.
</P>
<P>
Waiting for his first World Cup match against Austria on Thursday,
the young forward said:"I am not at alloverawed by playing in the
World Cup. I'm used to being close to the stars at Real Madrid."
</P>
<P>
Eto'o is on loan from Real Madrid to Spanish second division
team Leganes. He said:"It is very satisfying for me, but it is
strange as well. We wonder what is happening to us. To be the
youngest player out of the 704 players in the World Cup is very
special." 
</P>
</TEXT>
