<HEADLINE> Consumer Spending Up In Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- As living standards improve, people
in the suburbs of Xiamen in south China's Fujian Province are
spending more on quality in the goods and services they buy.
</P>
<P>
A survey of 140 households in the city's suburbs found that
home decoration and related facilities are becoming more popular
with farmers. In 1997, per capita spending on electricity and gas
was up 36 percent and 10 percent respectively from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
As diet and housing improve, farmers here pay more attention to
their dress. In 1997, they spent 8 percent more on clothing, 3
times as much on cosmetics and 44 percent more on jewelry.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications and medical insurance are also major
consumer items, the survey found, with telecommunication spending
up 8 percent last year and they spent 108 yuan on medical
insurance on average, up 74 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Per capita income for Xiamen's rural residents was 3,629 yuan
in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
