<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's members of Parliament
(MP) and Provincial Councils (PC) will be allowed to import tax
free vehicles, official sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The MPs will get permits that will provide complete tax
exemption for them when importing vehicles in the future, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The government has also decided to reimburse the 25-percent tax
which was levied on vehicles imported by the MPs earlier.
</P>
<P>
Formerly, the MPs' vehicles were imported under tax concessions
granted by the government but with a 25-percent tax.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 MPs and PC members will be entitled to the tax
refunding which is more than 100,000 rupees (1,500 U.S. dollars)
each.
</P>
<P>
Government officials however viewed this with dissatisfaction,
the sources added. 
