<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Striving to Improve Agricultural Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 11 (Xinhua) --Liaoning Province, an old
industrial base in northeast China, has decided to implement six
major industrialized agricultural programs with the help of
science and technology beginning from this year.
</P>
<P>
Wei Wenduo, director of Liaoning Provincial Commission of
Science and Technology, said they hoped that the move would help
the province advance the transition from traditional agriculture
to a highly-efficient modern one.
</P>
<P>
The six industrialized agricultural programs will include
industrialization of the production of forest frog-related
products, new-type fodders and fodder additives, cash crops and
related products, bio-pesticides, bio-organic compound fertilizers
and enriched natural fruit juice.
</P>
<P>
The province is expected to rake in an annual 8.5 billion yuan
in agricultural output value, 2.8 billion yuan of pre-tax profits,
and earn 42 million U.S. dollars from exports of agricultural
products by the year of 2000 if the six industrialized
agricultural programs are fully implemented, said experts.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning was saved from a loss of four billion kg of grain last
year owing to application of scientific and technological
achievements though its agriculture suffered severe natural
disasters, and was instead blessed with increases of 80,000 tons
of meat, 70,000 tons of poultry and eggs and 100,000 tons of
aquatic products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
