<HEADLINE> Poultry Overtakes Beef in Zimbabwe's Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Poultry has overtaken beef as
Zimbabwe's most valuable meat export, with producers selling 18
million U.S. Dollars worth of chickens, eggs and chicks to
southern African countries between January and March this year.
</P>
<P>
The commercial Poultry Producers' Association said Wednesday
that about 3,500 tons of chicken, 8.8 million chicks and 1.9
million table eggs were exported during the first three months
this year, the Herald newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chicken exports surpassed those of beef by 400 tons during the
same period agaisnt the background that Zimbabwe was unable to
meet its annual beef export quota of 9,000 tons to Europe
following a slump in demand caused by the outbreak of the ''mad
cow'' disease last year. Meanwhile, cattle producers are
rebuilding their dwindled herd following recent drought.
</P>
<P>
But the local demand for chicken is likely to grow further
with the proliferation of fast-food outlets, as in December last
year, the Zimbabweans consumed at least 1.5 million chickens.
</P>
</TEXT>
