<HEADLINE> China's First Jointly-Funded Railway Open to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WENZHOU, June 11 (Xinhua) -- China's first railway road to be
built with investment from Hong Kong, the Zhejiang provincial
government, and the Railway Ministry, opened to traffic today.
</P>
<P>
The railway connects the cities of Jinhua and Wenzhou in
Zhejiang Province. Work on it started in December, 1992. It passes
through five counties and cities in Zhejiang for 251 km.
</P>
<P>
Passenger trains depart Wenzhou and Jinhua each day.
</P>
<P>
The railway is expected to help the transport of natural
resources in 28 remote counties and three cities in Zhejiang and
to promote economic cooperation between Zhejiang and Jiangxi
provinces.  
</P>
