<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC, JCP Normalize Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China (CPC)
and Japanese Communist Party (JCP) have agreed to normalize
bilateral relations, according to official sources here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Dai Bingguo, member of the CPC Central Committee and head of
the International Department of the CPC Central Committee, and
Nishiguchi Hikaru, member of the Secretariat and head of the
International Department of the JCP Central Committee, held talks
on the issue of normalizing bilateral ties from June 8 to 10.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reviewed the history of bilateral relations,
exchanged opinions on the normalization of bilateral relations and
reached consensus in an earnest and practical manner and in the
spirit of proceeding from the overall situation of Sino-Japanese
friendship, ending the past and ushering in the future.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side made a conscientious summary of and
corrected its practice which did not conform to the Four
Principles of the party-to-party ties, especially the principle
of non-interference in each other's internal affairs, resulting
from the international environment and the "Cultural Revolution"
in the 1960s.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese side expressed appreciation for the sincere
attitude of the Chinese side.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that the issues left over from history
between the two parties have been resolved by and large. They also
agreed to normalize the relations between CPC and JCP.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will conduct friendly exchanges on the basis of
the party-to-party principles of independence, self-reliance,
total equality, mutual respect, non-interference in each other's
internal affairs proposed by the CPC, and on the basis of
self-reliance, independence, equality, non-interference in each
other's internal affairs proposed by the JCP.
</P>
<P>
The two sides hold that the development of bilateral relations
would make positive contributions to enhancing mutual
understanding and friendship between the two peoples and to the
promotion of long-term, stable and sound growth of good-neighborly
and friendly ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also reached consensus on the China visit by Fuwa
Tetsuzo, head of the Presidium of the JCP Central Committee, at
a time convenient to both sides.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
