<HEADLINE> More Foreign Tourists Visit Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Tourism in Lebanon is picking up as
more Arab and European tourists visit the country, the Daily Star
newspaper reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Lebanese Tourism Ministry showed that
the number of foreign visitors in the first four months this year
was about 146,000, nearly 10 percent more than the same period in
1997.
</P>
<P>
The number of European tourists rose by 27.4 percent from
January to April this year compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Arab tourists account for 36 percent of the total, followed by
Europeans, 35 percent.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese officials expect tourism to boom by more than 25
percent during the summer season this year. 
</P>
