<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Special Tourism Bus Lines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shanghai plans to
start 10 bus lines to link all tourism sites this year.
</P>
<P>
The first two lines are expected to open this month and the
others before October. They will distinct station marks and
tickets and will provide music and tourism site information for
passengers.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is becoming more common for Chinese and the city wants
to provide better services for sight-seers.
</P>
<P>
The first bus route, from Shanghai Stadium to Sheshan National
Tourism Zone, is expected to be popular. In the January-May
period, Sheshan had 300,000 tourists.
</P>
<P>
Other routes will run from Shanghai Stadium to the Pudong New
Area, Jiading, Qingpu, Chongming Island, and other scenic sites.
