<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Province Increasing Expressway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province is
using expressway construction to boost economic development in its
northern part.
</P>
<P>
Over the next five years, the northern part of the province is
expected to build 1,000 km. of expressways, at a cost of 30
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Work on the Taixing-Jingjiang expressway, the first six-lane
highway in the area, started in October 1996, at the beginning of
the construction program. It was followed by work on the 240-km
Lianyungang-Xuzhou Expressway, the 153-km Huaiyin-Jiangdu
Expressway, and the 1,688-m. Xinshuhe Bridge.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, 1.7 billion yuan was spent on these projects.
</P>
<P>
In the second half of this year, work on the
Lianyungang-Xuzhou, Xinyi-Haiyang, Nanjing-Suqian-Xuzhou, and
Nanjing-Jingjiang-Yancheng expressways will start.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has had some rapid economic development but with a lack
of balance in the southern and northern parts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
