<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Pudong Airport Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The first phase of construction
at the Pudong International Airport, Shanghai's largest
infrastructure project this century, which began on October 15,
1997, will be completed by the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The 32 sq km airport area in the Pudong new area is
expected to handle 70 million passengers and 5 million tons of
goods annually on its 4 north-south runways and 4 terminals.
</P>
<P>
The first phase will cost 12 billion yuan, mainly for a
4,000-meter runway, a 280,000 sq m terminal building, and other
facilities. It will allow a handling capacity of 20 million
passengers and 750,000 tons of goods annually.
</P>
<P>
Airline passenger traffic in Shanghai has gone up by 23.5
percent annually, and reached 12 million last year. Its Hongqiao
International Airport, which has a capacity of 9.6 million
passengers annually, is now overloaded and a new airport is needed
to relieve passenger congestion, which is what the Pudong
International Airport is for. 
</P>
</TEXT>
