<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Implement 43 Programs to Expedite Export Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's Export Promotion Bureau
(BEPB) has decided to implement 43 market development programs in
the July 1998-June 99 fiscal year to expedite the country's export
growth, said a BEPB press release reaching here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Of the programs, 27 are international trade fairs, five
single-country fairs, four commodity marketing missions and seven
minor bazars.
</P>
<P>
The private sector would participate in the fairs with
commodities like leather and leather goods, textiles, food items,
consumer goods, handicrafts, computers and household goods, which
would be held in various countries of Asia, Europe and the
Commonwealth of Independent States, the United States and
Australia.
</P>
<P>
The main objective to participate in the fairs was to
popularize Bangladesh's products in the prospective markets
throughout the world, the release pointed.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh maintained export growth at the rate of 16.75
percent in the last 10 months (till April) of the current fiscal
year.
</P>
<P>
Total export was about 4.18 billion U.S. dollars during the
period against 3.58 billion dollars in the corresponding period of
the last fiscal year, and total export for the fiscal year was
expected to reach 5.2 billion dollars. 
</P>
