<HEADLINE> Uruguayan, Argentine Fuel Companies Link </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan state petroleum
producer ANCAP signed an agreement of association Wednesday with
Argentine Petroleum distributor Sol Petroleo, with prospects of
becoming the main supplier of the Argentinian Fuel market.
</P>
<P>
The two companies will create a joint venture called ANCSOL,
which is expected to provide 35,000 cubic meters of gasoline a
month by 2001, and 54,000 cubic metres a month between 2006 and
2015, according to the agreement.
</P>
<P>
ANCAP will invest 20 to 25 million U.S. dollars to own 33
percent of the new company's shares. It will have to invest
another 60 million dollars to renovate "La Teja," its refinery, to
meet the quantity and quality demands of the Argentine market.
</P>
<P>
ANCAP would double or triple its exports if the joint company
proved to be a success. Its present export volume is around 70
million dollars, say reports. 
