<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cubas Proclaimed as President of Paraguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay's ruling Colorado
Party candidate Raul Cubas has been officially proclaimed as
President of Paraguay, according to news reports reaching here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Superior Court of Electoral Justice (TSJE) made the
announcement on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the general elections conducted last month, Cubas got
887,196 votes, 55 percent of the total. He beat his Democratic
Alliance rival candidate Domingo Laino by a margin of 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The result enables the ruling Colorado Party to continue its
50-year hold on power.
</P>
<P>
Cubas' running mate Luis Argana will resume as Vice-President
of Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
The TSJE also announced the parliamentary election results.
The Colorado Party increased its showing in the Senate with an
extra four seats, making 24, while those for the Democratic
Alliance reduced from 25 to 20.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 80 seats in the House, the Colorado Party increased
from 38 to 45, while those for the Democratic Alliance reduced
from 42 to 35.
</P>
<P>
Under the constitution, Cubas will be inaugurated on August
15. The new parliament will begin its first session on July 1.
</P>
</TEXT>
