<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama Passes Tough Environmental Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A General Environmental Law
was passed by Panama's Legislative Assembly Tuesday night,
creating new enforcing bodies and threating harsher punishments
for polluters.
</P>
<P>
The National Environmental and Natural Resources Authority
(ANARENA), an autonomous body, is created for regulating the use
of natural resources and protecting the environment, according to
the law, the information bulletin of the legislative assembly said.
</P>
<P>
The law also creates the National Environment Council formed by
three state ministers. It is responsible for recommending
appropriate national environmental policy to the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
A fine up to 10 million U.S.dollars may apply to those who
seriously pollute the environment. Fines amounting to one million
dollars or more will be decided by The national environmental and
natural resources authority.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, each company which begins a construction work
that may damage the environment will be obliged to conduct an
investigation of the possible impact of its work first.
</P>
<P>
An Environmental Treasury Office and five precincts in
different provinces will also be established, in accordance with
the law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
