<DOCNO> XIE19980611.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poor People Expected to Reach 30 Million in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The number of people living below
the poverty line is expected to reach 30 million if the economic
crisis persists, Antara News Agency Thursday quoted a government
official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Before the economic crisis began in mid-1997, only 22 million
of Indonesia's 202 million people were living below the poverty
line, said Coordinating Minister for the People's Welfare/Poverty
Eradication Haryono Suyono.
</P>
<P>
The figure even decreased to 17 million following the
implementation of programs aimed at eradicating poverty.
</P>
<P>
"But with the economic crisis, the figure is expected to go
back to 22 million. It could even reach 25 million. And if (the
crisis) continues over a long period, it could reach 30 million,"
the minister added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Education and Culture Minister Yuwono Sudarsono told
reporters here Wednesday that the government will support as many
as students as possible during the current economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said that around 30 percent of the country's 31 million
students had dropped out.
</P>
<P>
The financial programs announced by Sudarsono include
scholarships and the provision of operation costs for schools.
</P>
<P>
"Through the provision of financial support, the government
wants to prevent as many students as possible from falling victim
to the present economic crisis, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister said, implementation of the financial
programs must wait until the disbursement of funds from the
International Monetary Fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
