<HEADLINE> Brazil's Coffee Exports Drop in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's coffee exports in
May fell to 161.3 million U.S. dollars, a 46 percent drop from the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
According to Brazilian Federation of Coffee Exporters (FEBEC),
the volume of coffee exports fell to 989,700 bags (60 kilograms
per bag) from 1.4 million bags in May, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, the world's largest coffee producer and exporter, sold
4.3 million bags on the international markets in the first five
months of this year, 2.3 million bags fewer than 1997.
</P>
<P>
The reduced sales are attributed to the effects of the fall in
petroleum prices in international markets. 
</P>
