Expressway and Tianjin section of the Beijing-Shenyang expressway,
10 highways, 7 highway sections, two bridges, and waterworks with
a daily capacity of 200,000 tons of water, according to Wang
Jiayu, director of the Municipal Urban Construction Commission.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin's foreign investment has gradually shifted from
manufacturing to infrastructure, and over the past three years,
3.3 billion U.S. dollars worth of overseas investment has been
used for highways, bridges, and environmental protection, Wang
says.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's New World Group put 750 million yuan into three
trunk roads in the downtown area last year. 
