<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Banks Set Up Their Own Guild </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen Chinese commercial
banks in the city of Shenzhen, a major special economic
zone in Guangdong Province, have established their own guild and
have signed a self-discipline agreement.
</P>
<P>
The guild means that Shenzhen is forming a new way to supervise
the finance sector, one that is guided by the central bank but
based on self-discipline, according to Wu Jiesi, the vice-mayor of
Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
The city already has guilds in the insurance sector and for
foreign-funded banks.
