<HEADLINE> Venezuela, Colombia Conduct Joint Naval Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela and Colombia are
conducting a joint naval exercise along their mutual maritime
border, the Venezuelan Army announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Operation Caribe XII-98," which will end on June 15, is
intended to improve the naval combatant ability and strengthen
friendship and cooperation between two countries.
</P>
<P>
