<HEADLINE> London Not to Bid for 2008 Summer Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- London will not bid to host the
2008 Summer Olympics, the British Olympic Association (BOA)
announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
With Athens having already being awarded the 2004 Olympic Games
and the probability that another European city will be awarded
the 2006 Winter Games, the BOA decided there would be little point
in entering an expensive and potentially futile race to bring the
Olympic Games back to London, venue of the 1948 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The BOA chairman Craig Reedie said: "A later bid gives us the
opportunity to ensure that we have the time to plan effectively
to create a Games for London of the highest quality."  
</P>
</TEXT>
