<HEADLINE> Film Under Way on Culture of China's Ancient Villages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Shooting of a TV serial
displaying the culture of China's ancient villages has started at
the Zhuge Bagua Village in Lanxi City of east China's Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
The TV serial, titled "Roof and Root," will include 28 ancient
villages from across China to help modern people learn about the
architecture and folk customs of ancient Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Anmeng, producer of the serial, said that in June of 1999
China is expected to host the 20th Congress of the International
Architecture Association, the first time for the congress to be
held in Asia.
</P>
<P>
By then, Zhang said, the finished part of the serial will be
shown to architects from across the world to let them know
different development periods of China's ancient villages.
</P>
<P>
Experts here pointed out that, with the development of human
society, greater importance should attached to the protection and
research of ancient villages which recorded the process of human
civilization. 
</P>
