<HEADLINE> U.S. to Hold Wushu-Kungfu Festival, Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- An International Wushu-Kungfu
festival and championships will be held at Baltimore, the United
States, in August, the U.S. Wushu-Kungfu Federation chief
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The festival, scheduled for August 5-9, will include the U.S.
Nationals for National ranking, and the International Competition
open to athletes from all over the world, said Anthony T. Goh,
President of U.S.A. Wushu-Kungfu Federation at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
It will also feature three days of seminars by the world's
leading masters, a special Master's Demonstration, a Cultural Show
and the U.S. Wushu-Kungfu Hall of Fame Awards Ceremony.
</P>
<P>
In the two-day Championships on August 8-9, international
athletes will compete for International titles in traditional
Kungfu, contemporary Wushu, Taiji and Sanshou (full contact). In
all, nearly 300 divisions will be offered for children, men and
women, accommodating novices to advanced practitioners.
</P>
<P>
To date, 17 countries and regions have decided to send teams to
to the Festival and Championships, including Argentina,
Bangladesh, Barbados, Belgium, Brazil, Canada, China, Cote
d'Ivoire, India, Morocco, Nepal, the Netherlands, Spain, Sri
Lanka, Chinese Taipei, Ukraine and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
"We are very exited about the response we have received so far
from the international martial arts community," said Goh, who is
also President of Pan American Wushu Federation.
</P>
<P>
Athletes from the United States will be competing for National
titles and rankings in over 30 events, including traditional,
Wushu, internal and fighting divisions.
</P>
<P>
Goh said that a Baltimore Golden Cup is to award the five Grand
Champions in each of the main categories of Chinese martial arts:
Traditional Kungfu, Contemporary Wushu, Internal, Sanshou and
Light Contact Fighting.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the United States of America
Wushu-Kungfu Festival and the Chinese/Asian community in the
Greater Baltimore/Washington area will be hosting a wide variety
of cultural events throughout the Festival.
</P>
<P>
Traditional Chinese musical performances, Chinese painting and
calligraphy, Chinese medicine, and Chinese cuisine will be parts
of the Cultural Show.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Festival will create its own martial arts village
on the campus of Towson University during the August 5-9 period,
Goh said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
