<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Higher Against Mark, yen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar rose to hit a
six-week high against the German mark Wednesday as traders sought
the safe haven of the U.S. currency.
</P>
<P>
The dollar was changing hands at 1.7962 marks, up from 1.7805
Tuesday. During the New York trading session, the dollar hit its
six-week high of 1.7991 marks.
</P>
