<HEADLINE> IDB Supports Peace Process in Guatemala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) announced here Wednesday the approval of an 8 million
U.S. dollar loan to Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be utilized to help finance preinvestment
studies in priority areas as specified by national peace
agreements.
</P>
<P>
The studies will enable the government to rationalize
investments and present financing proposals in a timely way to the
international donor community so as to speed up the process of
mobilizing resources that will push forward the peace effort.
</P>
<P>
The peace agreements were signed in December 1996 in Guatemala
to end 36 years of armed violence, and the international donors
of the Consultative Group on Guatemala pledged 1.9 billion dollars
in financial assistance to back economic and social development in
the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
The IDB, which chaired the consultative group's meetings, has
approved several loans to assist the peace process, including 50
million dollars for the Community Development for Peace Trust
Fund.  
</P>
</TEXT>
