<DOCNO> XIE19980611.0265 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: African Leaders Heading for Strong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Apart from that, the summit managed to spare considerable time
and energy on economic issues.
</P>
<P>
The leaders in the end adopted a document which aims to
finalize the structure, operational modalities and various
policies of the one-year old African Economic Community (AEC).
</P>
<P>
The adoption of the decision may be seen as a sign to show
that African leaders have taken actions toward the realization of
their political will for the integration of the continent.
</P>
<P>
The latest development followed the encouraging achievements
African countries have made in the past few years, according to
host President Compaore.
</P>
<P>
The African development bank estimated the gross domestic
product growth in African countries at an average of 4.5 percent
in the past two years, up from that of less than two percent
during the 1990-95 period. The growth rate in 1998 and in the
medium-term will be around four to five percent.
</P>
<P>
Higher rate would be achieved if the political crises are duly
coped with and the heavy debt burden reasonably relieved.
</P>
<P>
As for the process of the continental economic integration,
the leaders called for efforts to strengthen the development and
inter- and intra-regional trade, and urged AEC to cooperate
closely with other regional economic organizations.
</P>
<P>
Promoting the development of the private sector has also been
recognized by the leaders as an effective means to boost African
economy.
</P>
<P>
The summit, meanwhile, did not forget to give sufficient
consideration to various social problems concerning poverty,
education, health, women and children, among others.
</P>
<P>
All these that were discussed and decided at the summit are of
critical importance to the future of Africa. People of the
continent, and the world at large, are watching with keen
interest the future development going on under the guidance of
the African leaders.
</P>
<P>
It is the hope of the people that African leaders, on their
part, will make convincing effort to put their commitment into
action for the realization of the common desire for a strong and
prosperous Africa.
</P>
<P>
If this comes true, there will be a bright future for Africa
and the world as a whole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
