<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Sink </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 10 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks fell sharply
Wednesday, with the Dow Jones industrial average dropping 78.22 to
8,971.70.
</P>
<P>
Investors began to worry again about company profits despite a
reassuring commentary by Federal Reserve chairman Alan Greenspan
and a big drop in interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow slipped 19 points on Tuesday after gaining 265 points
in the prior three sessions.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 fell 3.93 to 1,114.48, and the
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 27.50 to 1,773.26.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outnumbered advancers by more than a 2-to-1 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where NYSE volume totaled 607.56
million shares, up from 560.57 million on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 3.13 to 574.37, and the American
Stock Exchange composite index fell 7.22 to 706.85.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 5.66 to 451.08.
</P>
