<HEADLINE> 25 Cyprus' Beaches Awarded European Blue Flags </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-five beaches in Cyprus
were awarded "the Blue Flags of Europe" Wednesday for their fine
environmental quality.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony in the island's western coastal town of
Paphos, Speaker of the House of Representatives Spyros Kyprianou
stressed the need for protection of the environment against
pollution, saying that "Cyprus has the right to be proud because
it is in the lead as far as clean beaches are concerned."
</P>
<P>
The European Blue Flag campaign was launched in 1987 during
the European Year for the Environment and the "Blue Flag" has
become a European symbol of environmental quality.
</P>
<P>
The flags are awarded to beaches which fulfill a number of
criteria, including the quality of bathing water, environmental
education and information and beach area management and safety.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus, an island nation with beautiful beaches in the Eastern
Mediterranean, attracts more than 2 million foreign tourists
yearly, earning about 1.6 billion U.S. dollars which accounts for
20 percent of the island's gross domestic product. 
</P>
</TEXT>
