<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Meets With President of Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan Wednesday held talks with President of Tajikistan Emomali
Rakhamonov, who is here attending the United Nations Special
Session on the World Drug Problem.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, they discussed the decision of the Tajik
parliament to adopt an act which would effectively prohibit the
Islamic Revival Party, the largest component of the United Tajik
Opposition (UTO), from participating in the political life of the
country.
</P>
<P>
