<HEADLINE> OAU Favors 2 African Seats in UN Security Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 10 (Xinhua) -- African countries have
decided on the modalities of rotation for two seats as permanent
members they have claimed on the enlarged United Nations Security
Council.
</P>
<P>
Under the decision adopted at the just-ended 34th Summit of
the Organization of African Unity (OAU), nomination of candidates
in each of the five African sub-regions will be made by turn.
</P>
<P>
A list of candidates from the candidatures thus submitted to
OAU should be drawn up and a basket from which African leaders
will select two candidates from different sub-regions will be
prepared by the OAU General Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The same process of selecting African candidates for the
subsequent elections in the remaining sub-regions will also be
adopted according to the decision, reportedly being reached after
heated debate and discussions at the summit.
</P>
<P>
The duration of the mandate of the two candidates elected as
permanent members of the enlarged Security Council will be
determined by leaders of OAU member states, the document says.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
