<HEADLINE> Nigeria Destroys 60 Tons of Cannabis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has destroyed over
60 tons of cannabis in the past three years, Minister of Justice
Abdullahi Ibrahim told the on-going U.N. special session on the
world drug problem.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, with its anti-drug achievements recognized by the U.N.
International Narcotics Control Board, has been engaged in
regional and global collaboration in the anti-drug combat, he said
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria chaired a Western African sub-regional meeting at which
the Plan of Action on Drug Abuse Control for the period 1997-2001
was adopted, he said.
</P>
<P>
Cannabis is the most widely abused illicit drug in Africa, with
its trafficking being increased. 
</P>
