Kiriyenko said Wednesday that Russian-Belarus political ties
should be backed up by economic foundations.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko, who is on a two-day working visit to Belarus,
praised Moscow's good relations with Belarus.
</P>
<P>
He said there is no difference between the two countries and
any attempt to break their friendly bonds is doomed to failure.
</P>
