<HEADLINE> FIFA to Award Fastest Scorer at World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The scorer of the fastest goal at the
soccer World Cup finals will get more than the delight of netting in
the opening minutes.
</P>
<P>
The International Football Federation (FIFA) said on Wednesday that
a new official prize -- the Fastest Goal Award -- will make its debut
at the conclusion of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The fastest goal in the World Cup history was blasted by Vaclav
Masek of Czechslovakia only 15 seconds into a game against Mexico in
1962.
</P>
<P>
The FIFA will continue to hand out other five traditional awards,
which include Golden Shoe Award for the top scorer, Golden Ball Award
for the most outstanding player and Fair Play Award for the team with
the best fair play record.
</P>
<P>
There are also the Award for the Most Entertaining Team, won
undisputably by Brazil four years ago, and the Award for the Best
Goalkeeper. 
</P>
