<HEADLINE> Zambia's Stock Exchange Market Urged to Protect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Finance Minister Edith
Nawakwi Wednesday urged the stock market to ensure that investors
coming into the country are properly protected, according to
Zambia News Agency ZANA.
</P>
<P>
Opening the securities legislation-term review workshop in
Lusaka, Nawakwi said the investor is the most important player in
any securities market and that if he feels cheated, the market
would collapse.
</P>
<P>
"If the investor, however small or big, feels cheated and not
properly protected, they will not trade and the market will
collapse," said the finance minister.
</P>
<P>
She pointed out that strong statutory regulation of the
securities market is needed in order to promote investor
protection.
</P>
<P>
Nawakwi further called for the participation of all stake
holders in the regulation of the capital market.
</P>
<P>
The market must be fair, efficient and transparent apart from
being an attractive destination for local and offshore funds, the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
She added that the securities and exchange commission as an
advisory body must be operated in a manner that it will maximize
public confidence in the transparency and fairness of the market.
</P>
