<DOCNO> XIE19980611.0300 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Intensifies Anti-Drug Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Russia has intensified
anti-drug fight as drug abuse is growing in the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the U.N. special session on drugs here on
Wednesday, Deputy Foreign Minister Yury Ushakov said the Law on
Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances which meets
international standards entered into force in Russia in April,
among other anti-drug measures.
</P>
<P>
Russia attaches importance to building up a reliable anti-drug
barrier within the CIS (Commonwealth of Independent States)
framework, he said.
</P>
<P>
As a result of joint large scale operations of CIS law
enforcement agencies in recent years, hundreds of drug dealers
with worldwide connections have been neutralized, he added.
</P>
<P>
Russia has a total of 2 million people engaged in drug abuse,
with the annual growth rate of drug addicts moving from 10 to 15
percent in the beginning of the 1990s up to 60 percent in 1997, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Russia is located at the cross-roads of major traffic
itineraries of drug production and consumption where drug
smuggling from abroad is growing rapidly, the official noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
