Programme vehicle at the villages of Eiri and Hadab when they were
rained with bullets. The gunmen fled the scene.
</P>
<P>
The victims were all Sudanese, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
A U.N. aircraft flew immediately to Kadogle, carrying a doctor
and some U.N. officials to rescue the injured and and move the
dead bodies as well as conducting an immediate assessment of the
security stand in the area.
</P>
<P>
A detailed investigation of the accident will be made by the
U.N. officials within the few coming days. 
