<HEADLINE> Iranian Cabinet Discusses Possible Impeachment of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
gathered his cabinet members on Wednesday to discuss the possible
impeachment of Interior Minister Abdollah Nouri proposed by the
Majlis or parliament.
</P>
<P>
Khatami expressed his welcome to impeachment, saying that the
process of impeachment would help bring about the necessary
transparency in the matter, the Iranian official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that Nouri has the necessary capability to
elaborate on the stance and issues related to the Interior
Ministry," said the president.
</P>
<P>
He added that "although we may share differences of opinion on
the timing of the impeachment of the interior minister with some
of Majlis deputies, we hope that with the good-will of the Majlis
deputies and their alertness, the consequences would tilt to the
benefit of the country, the government and the people."
</P>
<P>
However, it was not clear whether the cabinet, which was formed
last August, has made any decision to counter the possible
impeachment.
</P>
<P>
The impeachment demand was raised by 31 conservative Majlis
deputies who claimed that "continuation of Nouri's service in the
post of interior minister is detrimental to tranquillity and
stability in the country."
</P>
<P>
In a swift response, Khatami said that his interior minister is
a "capable, outstanding personality of the revolution and the
system" and has been successful at his job.
</P>
<P>
Nouri was accused of creating tension in the society, making
provocative interviews and speeches in different provinces and
appointing inexperienced people to managerial posts at his
ministry. 
</P>
