<HEADLINE> S. African Ex-diplomat Charged With Espionage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Former South African diplomat
Rober Mcbride who was detained in south Mozambique this March for
suspected gun-running was formally charged with arms smuggling
and espionage Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified source with the Court of Maputo City disclosed
this, the Mozambican News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The source said the Mozambican Justice Ministry has formally
charged Mcbride with arms smuggling and espionage and that the
defense attorney of Mcbride has been notified of the charge.
</P>
<P>
Besides Mcbride, the source said, other two accomplices, Vusi
Mbatha and Alexandre Uambe, were also on trial.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, the court will review the argument
presented by the defense attorneys of the accused and then decide
whether there is enough evidence for sentencing them.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican judges have not been able to bring Mcbride to
court since he was detained in March in Machava prison in the
suburb of Maputo City. Therefore, Mcbride's defense attorney
Albano Silva demanded that the Supreme Court of Mozambique should
withdraw the case.
</P>
<P>
According to the Mozambican law, the accused could be
sentenced to 16 to 20 years of imprisonment on espionage and
eight to 12 years of imprisonment for arms smuggling. 
</P>
