with a fine sole performance. Norway levelled the score 1-1 just
before the interval thanks to an own goal from Amzine who tried to
clear the ball but headed the ball home instead.
</P>
<P>
After the interval, the two teams played as strongly as in the
first half. Hadda put Morocco 2-1 ahead in the 59th minute but only
to see his team's advantage faded away two minutes later.
</P>
<P>
The match was quite fierce and exciting as well. The two teams
stole the limelight on the day when defending champions Brazil
played the opening match against Scotland.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team, trying to win their fifth World Cup in
France, put up an under-par performance and won the match thanks to
good luck.
</P>
<P>
Tommy Boyd of Scotland scored an own goal to help lift Brazil to
a 2-1 victory though the Brazilians controlled most of the match.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo proved that he is the genius but failed to score. It
was Cesar Sampaio who scored for the Brazilian team.
</P>
<P>
Sampaio repeated his feat in the friendly against Germany when
he headed home a corner from Bebeto to put Brazil 1-0 ahead. But he
then brought down Kevin Gallacher in the penalty area and John
Collins converted the shot from the spot.
</P>
<P>
Then came Boyd to Brazil's rescue. He punched home a rebound to
give Brazil the win.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, Italy will play Chile at Bordeaux while Cameroon
takes on Austria at Toulouse. 
